@NODE "Installation" "Installation"

 @{B}[À @{BG SHADOW}@{APEN 2}  MatWB 3.0 @{BG HIGHLIGHT}@{APEN 1} Add-on package 2  @{BG BACKGROUND} À]@{UB}

 @{B}  À          @{U}INSTALLATION@{UU}         À @{UB}

 The installation is  the same as last
 t           i           m          e:

 Just click  the "InstallAdd-on"  icon
 and follow the onscreen instructions.

 The installer will  check if you have
 the "MATWB:" assign and if so it will
 assume  that   you   have   correctly
 installed                "MatWB 3.0".

 There should be  some directories  in
 the  assign  that  are  made  by  the
 original     "MatWB 3.0"    installer
 script.  If they are not present then
 the installer will  probably tell you
 something  like   "Unable  to  locate
 source/destination ......<blah blah>"
 and  will  abort.  Well,  fat chance!
 You shouldn't have messed with that!!

 I simply could have added  a check on
 that too,  but I didn't feel like it.

 If  the installer  does not  find the
 "MATWB:" assign it will ask you where
 you  wish  to  copy  all  the  stuff.


 If   you   don't  want  to   use  the
 installer and like to do it manually,
 well   that's   your   problem  then.


